rtrait of the youth culture of the Dutch Golden Age, at a time when the rising popularity of print made dissemination of new cultural ideas possible, while rising incomes and liberal attitudes created a generation of men behaving badly.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC-ND 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/4.0https://www.aup.nl/en/publish/open-access  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jun 2022) 0aMasculinityzNetherlandsxHistoryy17th century. 0aYoung men in art. 0aYoung menxAlcohol usezNetherlandsxHistoryy17th century. 0aYoung menxSexual behaviorzNetherlandsxHistoryy17th century. 0aYoung menzNetherlandsxHistoryy17th century. 7aHISTORY / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAUP eBook Package Backfile 2000-2013z978311070067108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAUP eBook Package Backlist 2000-2014z978311060651508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAmsterdam University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2015z97831106627880 cprintz978908964402240uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9789048515707?locatt=mode:legacyzOpen Access7040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9789048515707zOpen Access70423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9789048515707/original  a978-3-11-060651-5 AUP eBook Package Backlist 2000-2014c2000d2014  a978-3-11-066278-8 Amsterdam University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2015c2002d2015  a978-3-11-070067-1 AUP eBook Package Backfile 2000-2013c2000d2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-GOA